	   				   				   		</div>
	   		
	   		<div class="col460 clear">
	       		<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/f35c1b173b128e0d71d959547e57da62?s=50&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F1.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D50&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-50 photo' height='50' width='50' />	   				   			<p>“If a woman writes about herself, she’s a narcissist. If a man does the same, he’s describing the human condition.” Emily Gould</p>
<p>Much of the controversy over boobquake/brainquake/femquake reminds me of this quotation.  When women do anything to indicate that we&#8217;re proud of something about ourselves, we&#8217;re immodest, or lack humility, or narcissistic.  We&#8217;re still supposed to be demure and forgiving.  The same is rarely expected of men.</p>
<p>Damnit, I&#8217;m smart and have a great rack.  I&#8217;m quite proud of both.</p>
